oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: University of Chattanooga
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Black and white photograph of the University of Chattanooga campus in 1910.

University of Tennessee at Chattanooga was founded in 1886 as Chattanooga University, which was soon merged in 1889 with Grant Memorial University (now Tennessee Wesleyan University), becoming the Chattanooga campus of Grant Memorial University. In 1907, the school changed its name to University of Chattanooga. In 1964 the university merged with Zion College and later became Chattanooga City College. In 1969, the University of Chattanooga joined the University of Tennessee system and became the University of Tennessee at Chattanooga
